Nov 6

• Created an issue in the GitHub board related to the A11y (Accessibility) issue in the Role Assigning page.
• Added detailed comments regarding the work completed yesterday and updated the GitHub board.
• Found a new issue during care checking on the working page.
• Referred to the book “Designing Human-Centric Experiences” for insights related to Scribe.

Nov 7

• A slow-paced day.
• Commented on the related issue in GitHub.
• Checked possible solutions for the A11y (Accessibility) problem and had a discussion with @U07NP23BWQH regarding the same.

Nov 10
• Nothing much today.
• Checked the accessibility issues across the entire product.
• Reviewed the UX flow in the product to identify areas where issues are appearing.

Nov 11
• Traveling to Bangalore.
• Had a discussion with @Anagha M. about the A11y (Accessibility) issues and UI gaps in the product.
• Filed an issue regarding search behavior in the Multi-Field Support feature.

Next:
• Start working on the Search Component.
